<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>She announced her engagement to her boyfriend Simon Motson last week. </p>

<p>And Myleene Klass looked glowing as she strutted into Global Studios in central London on Saturday.</p>

<p>The Smooth Radio presenter, 42, put on a chic display in a black satin vest and flattering black trousers as she headed to work.  </p>

<p>Glowing: A newly-engaged Myleene Klass looked chic in an all-black ensemble and fedora as she headed to work at Smooth Radio on Saturday </p>

<p>The brunette beauty commanded attention by accessorising with a cream fedora and large black sunglasses.</p>

<p>Myleene completed her stylish look with a pair of strappy black heels and carried her favourite huge black Chanel bag on her arm.</p>

<p>The TV star upped the glamour with silver hoop earrings and looked in high spirits as she headed into the studios to present her radio show.  </p>

<p>Stepping out: The brunette beauty commanded attention by accessorising with a cream fedora and stylish black sunglasses</p>

<p>Her outing comes after last week she revealed she has got engaged to her boyfriend Simon Motson. </p>

<p>She admitted she was shocked when her partner, 45, popped the question last month on the fifth anniversary of their first date.</p>

<p>Speaking to Hello! magazine, Myleene told how Simon got down on one knee in their garden shed which he made into a replica of where they had their first date and surprised her with a nine-carat diamond ring.  </p>

<p>Heading to work: Myleene completed her stylish look with a pair of strappy black heels and carried her favourite huge black Chanel bag on her arm</p>

<p>All smiles: The TV star upped the glamour with silver hoop earrings and looked in high spirits as she headed into the studios to present her radio show</p>

<p>She said: 'We're engaged! I was absolutely blown away. He even replicated the dinner we had – burger and fries, followed by cherry pie.</p>

<p>'When he got down on one knee and started fumbling around under the table, I thought he was joking. Then I thought: "Oh my God, he's for real." I was completely speechless.'</p>

<p>Simon added: 'It's quite a blur but I think I said something along the lines of: 'Myleene Angela Klass, will you marry me?' And I had to say it again... and I think I said it a third time. Finally she said yes and we were both in tears.'</p>

<p>Confident: The Smooth Radio presenter, 42, put on a chic display in a stain black vest and flattering black trousers as she headed to work</p>

<p>Next step: Her outing comes after last week she revealed she has got engaged to her boyfriend Simon Motson</p>

<p>The PR man spared no expense for the proposal, even borrowing the table and chairs they used at Little House private members' club in Mayfair.  </p>

<p>Ever the romantic, Myleene told how Simon also decorated the shed walls with framed photos and filled their garden with fairy lights. </p>

<p>The couple's engagement has delighted Myleene's daughters Ava, 13, and Hero, nine, who have been determined to see the couple walk down the aisle while Simon's children, a 13-year-old son and nine-year-old daughter, are also thrilled. </p>

<p>Myleene and Simon began dating in 2015 after she split from husband Graham Quinn in 2012, and they welcomed their first child together, son Apollo, in August last year.    </p>

<p>Romance: The media personality admitted she was shocked when her partner popped the question last month on the fifth anniversary of their first date</p>
